The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       The City Diary
                A driver and his help were allegedly dragged out of a truck and beaten up by three sales tax officials looking for a bribe on BT Road, near Sinthee More, on Monday night. The tax officials had tried to stop the truck at Bagbazar, but the driver anticipated that he would be asked to pay a bribe and drove on. The officers chased the truck in an Ambassador and intercepted it near Sinthee More. The medical report that the two submitted with their complaint did not mention any injury, said a police officer.     The body of an unidentified boy, about 15 years old, was found on the Hooghly bank, near Shibpur burning ghat, on Monday afternoon. People at the ghat saw two boys jump into the river during high tide. When they did not come out even after a couple of hours, Shibpur police station was informed. The body was washed ashore during ebb tide. The other boy has not been traced.    Four youths with razors snatched Rs 2,500 and a cellphone from two passengers of a minibus on Foreshore Road on Tuesday morning. Two of them have been arrested.    Ajay Mandal, a 25-year-old security guard at a factory on Joybibi Road in Howrah, was arrested for allegedly strangulating a colleague, 23-year-old Abdul Hussan Mollah, on Tuesday afternoon. The two had an altercation over who would open the factory gate the next morning.    Two people were injured when the car they were travelling in was hit by a truck in Phoolbagan on Tuesday.                                                                                                                                                              
